 {"id":"bd-1bmj","title":"WebSocket close handshake: RFC 6455 close frame protocol","description":"# WebSocket Close Handshake Implementation

## Overview
Implements the RFC 6455 close handshake protocol ensuring clean connection termination
with proper close code propagation and timeout handling.

## Background & Motivation
WebSocket close is a two-way handshake: initiator sends Close, waits for Close response.
This prevents data loss and ensures both sides agree on termination. Critical for
cancel-correctness.

## RFC 6455 Close Protocol

### Close Frame Format
- OpCode: 0x08 (Close)
- Payload: Optional 2-byte status code + optional UTF-8 reason
- Status codes: 1000 (normal), 1001 (going away), 1002 (protocol error), etc.

### Handshake Flow
1. Initiator sends Close frame with status code
2. Receiver processes Close, sends Close frame in response
3. Initiator receives Close response
4. TCP connection can be closed

### Asupersync Integration
```rust
impl WebSocket {
    /// Initiate close handshake. Cancellation-safe.
    pub async fn close(
        &mut self,
        cx: &Cx,
        code: CloseCode,
        reason: Option<&str>,
    ) -> Outcome<(), WsError> {
        // 1. Send Close frame
        self.send_close_frame(code, reason).await?;

        // 2. Wait for Close response with timeout
        let close_timeout = cx.with_deadline(self.config.close_timeout);
        loop {
            match self.recv_frame(&close_timeout).await {
                Ok(Frame::Close(..)) => break,  // Got response
                Ok(_) => continue,               // Ignore other frames
                Err(Outcome::Cancelled) => {
                    // Cx cancelled during close - best effort
                    break;
                }
                Err(e) => return Err(e),
            }
        }

        // 3. Connection now in closed state
        self.state = WebSocketState::Closed;
        Ok(())
    }

    /// Handle incoming Close frame (as receiver).
    fn handle_close_received(&mut self, code: CloseCode, reason: &[u8]) -> Outcome<(), WsError> {
        // Echo close frame back
        self.send_close_frame(code, None)?;
        self.state = WebSocketState::Closed;
        Ok(())
    }
}
```

## Close Codes (subset)
- 1000: Normal closure
- 1001: Going away (cancellation)
- 1002: Protocol error
- 1003: Unsupported data
- 1006: Abnormal (no close frame received)
- 1007: Invalid payload data
- 1008: Policy violation
- 1009: Message too big
- 1010: Extension required
- 1011: Internal server error

## Cancellation Behavior
- Cx cancellation triggers close with code 1001
- Close handshake has bounded timeout
- After timeout, connection dropped without response
- No blocking forever on unresponsive peer

## Acceptance Criteria
