 {"id":"bd-1ckh","title":"HTTP/2 PUSH_PROMISE: incomplete implementation causes resource leaks","description":"# Security Bug: Incomplete PUSH_PROMISE Implementation

## Location
`src/http/h2/connection.rs:608-620`

## Vulnerability Description

PUSH_PROMISE handling is stubbed with a TODO comment:

```rust
pub fn process_push_promise(&self, frame: &super::frame::PushPromiseFrame)
    -> Result<Option<ReceivedFrame>, H2Error> {
    if self.is_client && !self.local_settings.enable_push {
        return Err(H2Error::protocol("push not enabled"));
    }
    // TODO: Handle push promise properly
    let _ = frame;
    Ok(None)
}
```

## Attack Vector

A malicious server can:
1. Send unlimited PUSH_PROMISE frames
2. Promised streams are never created or tracked
3. Stream IDs consumed without corresponding stream state
4. Eventually exhaust the stream ID space (2^31 per direction)

## Impact

- **Severity**: MEDIUM (resource exhaustion)
- **Exploitability**: Server-initiated only
- **Impact**: Client-side stream ID exhaustion, connection must be reset

## Root Cause

The implementation was left incomplete during initial development. PUSH_PROMISE 
requires:
1. Creating a reserved stream for the promised request
2. Tracking the promised stream ID
3. Associating with the original request
4. Proper state machine transitions

## Proposed Fix

Complete the PUSH_PROMISE implementation:

```rust
pub fn process_push_promise(&self, frame: &PushPromiseFrame) 
    -> Result<Option<ReceivedFrame>, H2Error> {
    if !self.is_client {
        return Err(H2Error::protocol("server received PUSH_PROMISE"));
    }
    if !self.local_settings.enable_push {
        return Err(H2Error::protocol("push not enabled"));
    }

    // Validate promised stream ID (must be even, unused)
    let promised_id = frame.promised_stream_id;
    if promised_id % 2 != 0 || promised_id <= self.last_server_stream_id {
        return Err(H2Error::protocol("invalid promised stream ID"));
    }

    // Check max concurrent streams
    if self.count_reserved_streams() >= self.local_settings.max_concurrent_streams {
        return Err(H2Error::refused_stream("too many pushed streams"));
    }

    // Create reserved stream
    let stream = Stream::new_reserved_remote(promised_id);
    self.streams.insert(promised_id, stream);
    self.last_server_stream_id = promised_id;

    Ok(Some(ReceivedFrame::PushPromise { ... }))
}
```

## Alternative: Disable PUSH_PROMISE

If server push is not needed, the simpler fix is to:
1. Always set SETTINGS_ENABLE_PUSH = 0
2. Reject any PUSH_PROMISE as protocol error

---

